    <article class="blog-post">
        <header>
            <h1>Their Lordships Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana in Germany</h1>
            <div class="lead-image">
                <img src="/images/article-details/166_Sri-Sri-Madana-Mohana.jpg" class="img-responsive">
                <div class="meta clearfix">
                    <div class="author">
                        <i class="fa fa-user"></i>
                        <span class="data">Manidhara Das</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="date">
                        <i class="fa fa-calendar"></i>
                        <span class="data">21 Aug 2018</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="comments">
                        <i class="fa fa-comments"></i>
                        <span class="data"><a href="#comments">1 Comments</a></span>
                    </div>                                
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>
        <div class="body"><p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">The appearance of Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana in Germany is as mysterious as Their L</font></font></font></span></span><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">ordships Themselves.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">How They came to Germany is not known to me, after all I was traveling on sankirtan all the time and it was not customary that our leaders shared their plans with us. As described in previous text, in times where every yatra had to have a castle to demonstrate its prosperity (?), Schloss Rettershof was rented and along that, rather suddenly, Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana appeared.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Hamsadutta das, our GBC, wrote to Srila Prabhupada about his plan to install these Deities. Srila Prabhupada wrote him back that this is not the time to do so, and as Germany is becoming glorious by book distribution, this should be the main focus of the yatra. Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s letter arrived.......after the installation of Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana. Did They come anyway, even Their installation was not at that point authorized by the Founder Acharya?</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">This is not up to me to judge. But Their Lordships did indeed exhibit amazing potency, blessing us over and over again with Their presence as we every week dove into the jungle of German streets to face opposition and challenge again.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">When Srila Prabhupada arrived second time in Germany in 1974, the time I got initiated, He was already greeted by Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana and didn&rsquo;t objected to Their presence at all.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Being worshiped at the highest standard by Astaratha Prabhu, we simply admired the distant forms of Their Lordships. It&rsquo;s never a &ldquo;chance&rdquo; that Radha-Krsna appear in Their particular forms in particular countries. Overlooking the &ldquo;Darshan&rdquo; book which shows the whole variety of Deities in various countries, it cannot go unnoticed how Krsna corresponds to the particular nature of the local residents, however materially conditioned it may be. Srila Prabhupada noticed that when He said that &ldquo;Krsna came to France because He heard the French girls are most beautiful&rdquo; :-)</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">And so Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana corresponded to the German inherent nature inviting mysticism and heroic pathos of self-sacrifice as several times demonstrated in the history of this country.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Krsna is all attractive and He knows best the nature of a nation, the nature of us all, both the conditioned ones and the original spiritual ones.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">And so Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana were &ldquo;not easy to worship&rdquo; as one Indian visiting pujari commented.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Astaratha Prabhu&rsquo;s devotion was truly amazing. He hardly ever left the temple, worshiping these Deities day and night. </font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Once I stayed with him in a room overnight. While I was sleeping, I suddenly woke up and heard him in his sleep speaking softly planning what kind of outfit the Deities may wear next day.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">The standards of Deity worship as given by Srila Prabhupada were followed by Astaratha Prabhu exactly. No silas were placed on the altar, as Srila Prabhupada didn&rsquo;t authorize Their worship, and Hamsadutta&rsquo;s idea to worship Laksmiji on the altar in form of a conch was quickly abandoned as well. The Deities were as Srila Prabhupada said &quot;looking as printed&rdquo;, standing frontally to receive worship. Not even slightly turned, dressed luxuriously in silks, velvet and pearls in most opulent way. After all Srila Prabhupada, originally hesitant to install Sri Sri Radha Krsna in ISKCON at all, finally established that in ISKCON we DON&rsquo;T worship Sri Sri Radha Krsna in Their intimate Vrndavana mood, but our worship is conducted in the mood of Laksmi Narayan, meaning in mood of reverence and opulence.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">This was strictly followed, and Astaratha Prabhu and his assistants, later on Rohini Devi Dasi to be especially mentioned, did amazing service as demonstrated on many photos from those days.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">For us, the sankirtan devotees, the Deities were the Lordships where we placed our prayers for improvement of our book distribution. We used to carry the newly printed books through the whole Sunday Program in our hands. Seeing them being non-different from the Deities, we chanted with them and we danced with them in kirtan joyfully. Standing in front of Sri Sri Madan Mohana we prayed</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">:</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> &ldquo;My dear Sri Sri Radha Madan</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">a</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> Mohana, please, if you so desire, let me distribute 500 of these wonderful </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">books </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">next week</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">.&rdquo;</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000">&hellip;<font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">...and They did!</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">A prominent custom was that whoever distributed most books in that particular week was allowed to perform </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">puja</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> to Their Lordship during Mangala Arotika ceremony. For almost four years in Germany it was... me :-) </font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">First time it happened and I was the number one man, I was terrified.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Freshly showered with new tilak, I stood in the Deity room at 4 A.M. in front of Astaratha Prabhu, telling him: &ldquo;I cannot do this. I have no idea about Deity worship, (as I don&rsquo;t have until today), I am not purified </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">enough.&rdquo;</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Astaratha Prabhu looked at me firmly and said: &ldquo;You were the whole week distributing Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s books, you are purified enough!&rdquo; Such was the mood </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">in </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">those days.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">I still objected: &ldquo;But you chant all these different mantras during the worship, I know nothing of </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">this.&rdquo;</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">He looked at me somewhat pragmatically and said: &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t bother, just chant Hare </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Krsna.&rdquo;</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">And so he showed me the different items on the plate and the sequence how they should be offered.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">The curtain went open and I stood there in front of Their Lordship with the devotees chanting Samsara prayers in the dark temple room. It was a tremendous experience. I had hard time to control my tears as </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">then </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">I wouldn&rsquo;t be able</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">to see the different items anymore. It was so amazing to be so close to Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana. Especially Radharani&rsquo;s smile was the sweetness personified. She looked eagerly, almost </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">excited,</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> towards the devotees, appreciating the tremendous kirtan. (Yes, thanks to Hamsadutta&rsquo;s presence the kirtans were roaring already in the early mangala arotika, as devotee</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">s</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> couldn&rsquo;t suppress their ecstasy. Kirtan meant those days lots of dancing</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">,</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> and shouts of joy were heard all the </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">time.)</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> </font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Krsna was more reserved, simply casting His glances filled with blessings and approval upon the chanting sankirtan warriors.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Finally I blew the conch and returned to Astaratha, simply apologizing for all the offences I have done during the puja. Next Sunday I was on the altar again at this hour, only to come back week after week.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Unavoidabl</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">y</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> after some time I was effected by certain pride, as prior to reading sankirtan results after the Sunday morning lecture, it was already clear who was number one </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">of </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">that week. It was the devotee who did perform the mangala arotika, and that was me :-) And so I offered the camara at the end of arotika, </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">and while offering it to the devotees with big smile on my face I </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">fann</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">ed</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> the air to all my &ldquo;opponents&rdquo; :-), to all those who tried to defeat me in numbers of distributed books every week.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Certainly, after some years my pride was rectified as far more empowered sankirtan men joined our forces, bringing the book distribution to levels hardly ever to be imagined. Thousands and millions of books went out every week all over the world</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">,</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> with German yatra being always in midst of the action.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Actually, during the management of Harikesha das in his North European zone, reaching from previous Yugoslavia up to Island, more books got published and distributed </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">than</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> </font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">across</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> the whole planet during Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s presence. To be part of something so gigantic is most inspiring and wonderful.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s presence can be recognized by the presence of book distribution</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">,</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> as He himself clearly stated</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">:</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> His books are embodying His heart. Whenever book distribution is going on, Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s heart is beating strong</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">,</font></font></font><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3"> and those who are blessed to be part of His pulls are the most blessed souls on this planet.</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p lang="en" style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Sri Sri Radha Madana Mohana ki jaya!</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;"><span style="background: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="line-height: 100%;"><font color="#000000"><font face="Helvetica, serif"><font size="3">Srila Prabhupada&rsquo;s book distribution ki jaya!</font></font></font></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
    </article>

